  <tr>
    <td colspan="2"><p>The ultimate addition to any braai, our full butterfly chicken is enough to share between 4-6 people and a must have for grilling on sunny days.</p>
<p>No more standing around the fire waiting for the chicken to cook! Our chicken flattie has been expertly prepared in our signature style and dry rub and par cooked to lock in the flavour, making a simpler and faster way to grilling experience.</p>
<p>Sourced from the highest quality suppliers, our chicken flattie comes vacuum packed and ready to cook with our signature spices. For additional flavours, check our signature sauces.  </p>
<h3>How to cook: </h3>
<h4><strong>Grill:</strong></h4>
<p>Over a hot fire or coals, place the chicken ribs down on the fire and turn regularly. If you are using a sauce, baste the chicken each time you turn to avoid drying the meat out and crispen the skin.</p>
<h4>Oven:</h4>
<p>Crank the oven to 200(C) degrees; place the chicken in an oven suitable dish, and cover with foil, cook in the oven for 20 minutes, remove the foil for the last 5 minutes to get it crispy. </p>
<p>If you are using a sauce, baste the chicken beforehand. After 10 minutes, remove and baste again, leave the foil off for the last 10 minutes.</p></td>
